NAME
       ls - list directory contents

SYNOPSIS
       ls [PATH]

DESCRIPTION
       List the entries of the current directory, or of PATH when
       one is given.

       This is a simplified ls with no options. Directories are
       shown with a trailing slash (/); files are shown by name.

       If PATH points to a file, its name is printed. If PATH does
       not exist, an error is shown.

SEE ALSO
       cd(1), cat(1), pwd(1), man(1)

